text:
:bangbang: Help needed!
Looks like HubSpot CMS is not serving the same page whether it’s been requested on desktop or on mobile. Has anyone ever experienced something silimar?
I have an image, inside a repeater, inside a module.
The image is showing in the source when I load the page on desktop.
But when I open the page on mobile, or even using the dev tool emulating a mobile, the image is missing.
Here’s what my hubl file looks like (simplified for the sake of readability):
```{% if module.slides|length == 1 %}
    {% if module.slides[0].video %}
        {% if module.slides[0].video_thumbnail.src %}
             IMAGE HERE
        {% else %}
             NO IMAGE
        {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
{% endif %}```
When I open the page on desktop, it shows “IMAGE HERE” ; but when I open it on mobile it shows “NO IMAGE”.
Could it come from the image format? Although I tried a a few different images and the problem is the same.
Could anyone provide some help it would be greatly appreciated :raised_hands:
